Q-5) Java Program To Swap Two String Variables Without Using Third Variable

Input :

String a = “java” ;
String b = “program”

Output :

String a = “program”
String b = “java”


public class SwapStrings {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String a = "java";
        String b = "program";

        // Step 1: Concatenate both strings
        a = a + b;

        // Step 2: Extract original 'a' from combined string
        b = a.substring(0, a.length() - b.length());

        // Step 3: Extract original 'b'
        a = a.substring(b.length());

        System.out.println("String a = " + a);
        System.out.println("String b = " + b);
    }
}

